article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 62, SE Louisiana 51
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Walt Harris scored 18 points and Jereal Scott added 12 to lead Stephen F. Austin to a 62-51 victory against Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday night. Jordan Glynn had six points and 12 rebounds for the Lumberjacks (13-5, 3-2 Southland). Patrick Sullivan had 20 points and Rodney Jones 10 for Southeastern Louisiana (10-8, 2-3). Stephen F. Austin won the rebounding battle 36-19, had a 28-12 edge in points in the paint and 18-2 advantage in second-chance points. The Lumberjacks took control as the Lions suffered a 5:41 scoring drought in the second half. Eddie Williams had four of Stephen F. Austin's eight points during the stretch, which gave it a 56-45 lead with less than six minutes remaining.
